Advisers to President Tomislav Nikolic described being 'thrown around the cabin' on Friday . 
  Plane carrying him to Italy was forced to turn back after co-pilot spilled coffee on the instrument board . 
  Pilot Bojan Zoric said he accidentally turned off the autopilot as he wiped it down . 
  Plane landed safely back in Belgrade but Nikolic was unable to meet Pope Francis . 
 